description._content: Description: Hanukkah lamp consisting of a backplate depicting twisted columns (each with star of David at base) flanking menorah with figure of Moses, above each menorah is a star of David. Above: cube-shaped oil container, above which is a crown flanked by rampant deer. All set against open scrollwork. Object origin: Israel Date: approximately 1960 Medium: metalwork with copper, silver, brass Repository: Yeshiva University Museum Call Number: 2000.424 Persistent URL: access.cjh.org/412991 Rights Information: No known copyright restrictions; may be subject to third party rights.
